            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1145">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">119.2/2–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-14T13:00:00+08:00">February 14, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 14—4:04 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>515. No radio communications any kind ever transmitted behalf Chinese Government
                    over Mukden radio circuit (Peiping 192, February [8]). Complete file all traffic
                    held Shanghai control station.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 515; repeated Canton 56, Peiping 36, pouched Nanking 362.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
